'''Lysa Arryn''', nĂŠe '''Tully''', is a recurring character in the [[Season 1|first]] and [[Season 4|fourth]] seasons. She is played by guest star [[Kate Dickie]] and debuted in &quot;[[The Wolf and the Lion]].&quot; LysaÂ was the Lady Regent of the Vale, ruling on behalf of her young son [[Robin Arryn]]. She doted on her son and pursued a policy of isolationism since the death of her husband [[Jon Arryn]]. She presided over the [[First Trial by Combat of Tyrion Lannister|trial]] of [[Tyrion Lannister]] for the murder of [[Jon Arryn]] and the attempted murder of [[Bran Stark]]. He proves his innocence in a trial by combat. Lysa refused to commit her forces to aid her sister [[Catelyn Stark]] in the [[War of the Five Kings]].

